  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6572.99 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma between 6550-6570 (all amplifying strikes), dealers are forced to buy this dip aggressively as their short gamma positions require delta hedging in the same direction as price moves. The breakout regime confirms dealers are structurally short gamma, meaning they'll continue buying rallies and selling dips, creating momentum-driven moves rather than mean reversion. Key battle zone is the 6560-6600 corridor where max negative gamma (-28.6B) transitions to max positive gamma (+28.0B) - a break above 6600 would flip dealers to selling mode and likely cap upside momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent whipsaws as dealers amplify every move until price breaks definitively above 6600 or below 6550.",
